About the Location  Bengaluru, the Silicon Valley of India, is growing very fast in the IT/ITeS sector. The city is the hub of major IT giants who have set up their establishment here. In fact, the start-ups and many small companies are also eventually shifting their base from different parts of India to Bengaluru due to its growing infrastructure and market opportunity.  This is pushing the employment opportunities, which in turn, is increasing the demand for residential real estate in India. Electronic City is one such location in Bengaluru that has the largest industrial technology parks and over 200 IT/ITeS companies currently operational. The area consists of zones that have few renowned companies functioning such as Wipro Ltd, Tata, Genpact, HCL Technologies, General Electric, etc. Not only this, there are many other companies functioning in the region in various industries as well.  Due to the growth of commercial space, people have migrated to Bengaluru for better job opportunities. This has also pushed the real estate residential demand in Electronic city and its nearby areas.  Development in and around Electronic City is immense, major reputed educational institutions and medical facilities are located nearby. At Doddathougur road one can easily find various social infrastructure such as colleges, institutes, hospitals, restaurants & all sorts of shops for your daily needs.  Electronic city has great connectivity to the other parts of the city too. Electronic City Flyover connects the Hosur Road within 3-4 minutes and Silk Board in 10-12 minutes. The Electronic City flyover connects the Nice Ring Road touching further to Nice Bangalore-Mysore Expressway and other parts of the city through the Outer Ring Road. Electronic City has good road connectivity. It has a great frequency of Bangalore Metropolitan Transport Corporation (BMTC) and Bangalore International Airport Ltd (BIAL) buses.  The easy connectivity is making Electronic City a favorite destination among the residents and working professionals.  The working class usually wants to stay near to their workplace. The mid-level IT professional opts for affordable properties here. The upcoming metro connectivity to Electronic City will be a relief for the daily commuters. The phase 2 of Bengaluru Metro will connect 16 stations, thus, improving the connectivity.

Prestige Pine Wood is a High-Rise Residential Development in the midst of a well-established and sought after location, at Koramangala (Jakkasandara) Bangalore. Koramangala, located at the heart of the city has good proximity to IT hub and recreational zones. Prestige Pine Wood consist of 256 premium apartments and offers a combination of 2, 2.5, 3 and 4 bedroom units, and sits on a prime land of 2.5 acres and is placed in such a way that it provides maximum natural light and ventilation. The master plan of these properties offers the finest view of the adjacent landscaped parks, and the overall architecture and space planning has been designed explicitly to spell luxury. A well-integrated club house is closely knit within the towers with modern amenities such as a mini theatre, banquet hall, gymnasium, billiards & TT room, along with a swimming pool and a spa. The building facade is contemporary with straight lines and an imaginative use of understated colours and textures have been used that underpin the word Pine Wood. The Landscape and views that are captured from all around only enhance the feel of space and unobstructed expanse making it a truly pleasurable place to be. The use of modern tasteful materials and finishes finally complete the overall theme that the design seeks to achieve. Explore this micro-site to discover more about Prestige Pine Wood.

Ramagondanahalli is a booming residential area in Bangalore that is witnessing several Real Estate developments. There are two major four lane roads connecting Bangalore city with the locality namely Whitefield road via Mahadevapura and Varthur road (HAL Old Airport Road) via Marathahalli. Both roads intersect with Karnataka State highway 35 (SH 35) which runs in the North-South direction (Siddlaghatta in the north to Anekal in the south). Various shopping malls like The Forum Value, Phoenix Market City, Park square mall and Inorbit Mall are also located near the area. Ramagondanahalli also has extensive city bus connectivity with a wide range of services offered by BMTC. A Traffic and Transit Management Centre (TTMC) in EPIP is now functional with schedules connecting it with most areas of the city. The much anticipated Namma Metro project is expected to cater to the locality under Phase 2. The Purple line will be extended from Byappanahalli to Whitefield covering 13 stations in between. There are a number of International Schools in Whitefield like Whitefield Global School - Channasandra Road, EuroSchool Whitefield, Gopalan International School, Mount Litera Zee School.
